  "style": "IEEE",
  "texts": [
    "It is worth mentioning that even if machines could, under certain conditions, be agents, the possibility of them being moral agents is much more unlikely.",
    "Let us not forget also, that one main reason for the emergence and growth of AI-Ethics is the close relationship between intelligence and morality [47].",
    "Today, AI models seem cogent, but their most powerful characteristic is the hand that empowers them with the next appointed task.",
    "Therefore, AI-Ethics should be focused on Human-Ethics instead, and thus must be confronted with anthropocentric logic to be able to offer to our society all the benefits that a scientific field entails, but without dire consequences.In the upcoming world of AI powered businesses, AI education, AI controlled cars, AI authored books, and AI empowered society, there exist no binary solutions on what is ethical and who is responsible if something goes wrong.",
    "Aristotle first instilled the anthropocentric principle into the philosophy of ethics, and walking on his steps, there must be a constant seeking for the middle ground between human benefit from technological progress and the moral decline this technology brings in the form of wealth by using other peoples' work."
  ],
